.TH "thread_group_exited" 9 "thread_group_exited" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
thread_group_exited \- check that a thread group has exited
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" thread_group_exited
.BI "(struct pid *pid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pid" 12
tgid of thread group to be checked.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Test if the thread group represented by tgid has exited (all
threads are zombies, dead or completely gone).
.SH "RETURN"
true if the thread group has exited. false otherwise.
